lead_paragraph: Matt Moore, making his first start in almost five years, threw a career-high four touchdown passes Saturday night as the Miami Dolphins ensured they would keep pace in the AFC wild-card race with a 34-13 rout of the New York Jets in East Rutherford, New Jersey.

headline.main: Dolphins Stay in Playoff Hunt With 34-13 Rout of Jets
